WEBVTT

00:00:17.490 --> 00:00:21.000
Duramente is set for the Triple Crown!!

00:00:37.430 --> 00:00:47.650
Umamusume

00:00:41.270 --> 00:00:47.650
Pretty Derby

00:01:55.940 --> 00:01:57.070
Listen up!

00:01:57.070 --> 00:02:00.170
Stick to running in your ideal way
and build out the race from there!

00:02:00.170 --> 00:02:02.400
You can't let the others
draw you into their pace!

00:02:02.400 --> 00:02:03.260
Right!

00:02:03.260 --> 00:02:05.060
N
I
C
E

00:02:05.060 --> 00:02:07.060
Stupid, stupid, stupid!

00:02:14.750 --> 00:02:17.490
D
U
R
A
M
E

00:02:23.990 --> 00:02:25.150
I wasn't even close.

00:02:25.620 --> 00:02:29.290
She was so far in front. I couldn't reach her.

00:02:29.740 --> 00:02:31.770
I don't know... if I can ever...

00:02:42.330 --> 00:02:43.830
You okay, Kitasan?

00:02:45.550 --> 00:02:46.240
Well,

00:02:46.240 --> 00:02:50.970
I was thinking we maybe had you working a
little too hard in the run-up to the Derby.

00:02:50.970 --> 00:02:54.450
And that maybe it's keeping
you from being able to focus.

00:02:54.450 --> 00:02:55.900
No, I'm...

00:02:55.900 --> 00:02:58.500
Let's prioritize recuperating for now.

00:02:58.500 --> 00:02:59.990
You can head back for today.

00:03:02.790 --> 00:03:04.030
I understand.

00:03:21.720 --> 00:03:24.220
Can this emperor
surpass the last?

00:03:21.720 --> 00:03:24.220
Tokai Teio

00:03:24.220 --> 00:03:26.530
Teio-san's races

00:03:28.190 --> 00:03:31.680
Today's feature is on the winner of
the Satsukishou and Japanese Derby,

00:03:31.310 --> 00:03:35.810
DURAMENTE SPECIAL FEATURE

00:03:31.310 --> 00:03:35.810
Triple Crown Spotlight!

00:03:31.680 --> 00:03:35.810
Duramente, who has built anticipation
for a Triple Crown win this year.

00:03:36.080 --> 00:03:38.080
With remarkable speed and power,

00:03:38.080 --> 00:03:40.610
and otherworldly running that
entrances those who see it...

00:03:40.070 --> 00:03:51.100
HER PERFORMANCE IN THE CLOSING OF THE RACE

00:03:40.070 --> 00:03:51.100
THOUGH WILD, SHE DEMONSTRATED ENOUGH POWER
TO TAKE THE DOUBLE CROWN

00:03:41.070 --> 00:03:43.370
Today, we're going to examine her appeal,

00:03:43.370 --> 00:03:48.530
which would be fair to compare to that of
star horse girls of previous generations

00:03:48.530 --> 00:03:51.040
like Symboli Rudolf,
Tokai Teio, and Narita Bryan.

00:03:57.600 --> 00:04:01.090
I looked up to him. I wanted to be like him.

00:04:02.990 --> 00:04:04.970
And I thought I actually could...

00:04:07.850 --> 00:04:13.040
Dazzling on the stage,
drawing everyone's attention...

00:04:13.040 --> 00:04:19.340
I wanted to be the same
kind of star my dad was.

00:04:20.110 --> 00:04:25.170
I saw that dream realized,
in a certain form, on that day.

00:04:23.110 --> 00:04:25.780
Fill in the missing space.

00:04:23.110 --> 00:04:25.780
East

00:04:23.110 --> 00:04:25.780
West

00:04:23.110 --> 00:04:25.780
South

00:04:23.110 --> 00:04:25.780
North
\h\h\h\h(Kita)

00:04:23.620 --> 00:04:27.080
Tokai Teio is demonstrating a real
aptitude at straightaways here.

00:04:27.080 --> 00:04:29.170
There are three runners behind
her battling for second.

00:04:29.170 --> 00:04:30.540
It's Tokai Teio!

00:04:30.540 --> 00:04:32.060
Tokai Teio is taking off!

00:04:32.060 --> 00:04:37.560
She's demonstrating her superior potential
by getting one... no, two lengths' lead!

00:04:37.560 --> 00:04:39.040
That's incredible!

00:04:39.040 --> 00:04:44.050
Tokai Teio shows why she was favored
to win by finishing in first!

00:04:44.050 --> 00:04:46.280
You've gotta hand it to her!

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:51.660
That was really amazing! To run
like that in her first race...

00:04:51.660 --> 00:04:52.860
Wow...

00:04:53.350 --> 00:04:56.150
Wow, wow! That was just amazing!

00:04:53.920 --> 00:04:55.810
I was a fan after a single glimpse of her.

00:04:56.150 --> 00:04:59.270
She was strong, beautiful, and cool.

00:05:00.610 --> 00:05:05.080
As another horse girl, I thought about how
much I wished I could run just like her.

00:05:06.530 --> 00:05:08.700
"I want to be like Teio-san."

00:05:08.700 --> 00:05:10.370
Even now,

00:05:10.370 --> 00:05:11.990
Goal

00:05:10.370 --> 00:05:14.350
I keep thinking about how I want to take
the steps I need to be as great as her.

00:05:15.050 --> 00:05:19.080
I want to stand at her side. I want to see
the same sights and feel what it's like.

00:05:19.380 --> 00:05:21.360
I want to be a horse girl like her!

00:05:22.260 --> 00:05:26.220
Spring, summer, fall, and winter...

00:05:26.220 --> 00:05:28.720
On clear days and rainy ones...

00:05:28.720 --> 00:05:31.800
Whether I felt good or bad...

00:05:31.800 --> 00:05:35.540
When I was alone, or with my friends...

00:05:35.540 --> 00:05:41.720
The thing I yearned for the most
was to chase after Teio-san.

00:05:42.330 --> 00:05:45.220
The way she shined so bright, like a miracle.

00:05:45.640 --> 00:05:50.380
And she was always in the distance, but...

00:05:50.910 --> 00:05:53.770
I thought if I worked hard,
I could reach her someday.

00:05:54.200 --> 00:05:58.590
I could catch up to my ideal...
become like the person I idolize.

00:05:59.130 --> 00:06:01.320
That's why I've kept running.

00:06:01.960 --> 00:06:05.550
Welcome to the Tracen Academy open campus!

00:06:05.550 --> 00:06:07.190
What are your names?

00:06:07.190 --> 00:06:08.710
I'm Kitasan Black!

00:06:08.710 --> 00:06:10.430
I'm Satono Diamond!

00:06:11.210 --> 00:06:13.260
Okay! I'll remember you two!

00:06:15.770 --> 00:06:17.140
Starting on the outside hasn't
been any problem for her!

00:06:17.420 --> 00:06:21.640
Tokai Teio... has won the Japanese Derby!

00:06:20.150 --> 00:06:20.850
Japanese Derby

00:06:21.640 --> 00:06:24.820
Tokai Teio! Tokai Teio is in the lead!

00:06:24.820 --> 00:06:28.150
Tokai Teio makes a miraculous return!

00:06:27.950 --> 00:06:29.820
Arima Kinen

00:06:30.360 --> 00:06:32.070
She was so amazing...

00:06:32.740 --> 00:06:34.810
Blindingly bright.

00:06:35.580 --> 00:06:38.080
Entrance Ceremony

00:06:37.050 --> 00:06:39.020
We're finally here, Dia-chan.

00:06:39.020 --> 00:06:41.690
Yeah. Let's work hard together, Kita-chan.

00:06:43.530 --> 00:06:49.470
I enrolled in Tracen Academy and made my debut,
so maybe I had gotten a little closer.

00:06:49.470 --> 00:06:53.470
I thought so, and I was focused
on what was in front of me.

00:06:54.370 --> 00:06:55.940
I ran as hard as I could.

00:06:56.680 --> 00:06:58.310
I've run all this time.

00:07:01.400 --> 00:07:05.570
But... I realized it, on some level.

00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:11.800
I...

00:07:13.190 --> 00:07:14.170
don't think...

00:07:20.510 --> 00:07:22.160
I was able to do it.

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:28.420
I'm heading out to run.

00:07:28.420 --> 00:07:29.790
Be safe!

00:07:31.850 --> 00:07:33.790
Kitasan's been down lately.

00:07:33.790 --> 00:07:36.400
I hope she's eating properly.

00:07:36.400 --> 00:07:38.780
She's bound to be over her exhaustion,

00:07:38.780 --> 00:07:41.410
but I think her motivation
hasn't bounced back yet.

00:07:41.410 --> 00:07:44.600
If she pushes too hard in that condition,
she could seriously hurt herself.

00:07:44.600 --> 00:07:46.190
She needs to take her time.

00:07:46.190 --> 00:07:50.600
You're not worried?
Your favorite kouhai is troubled.

00:07:50.600 --> 00:07:51.770
It's okay.

00:07:52.610 --> 00:07:55.030
I know Kita-chan will be all right.

00:07:59.050 --> 00:08:01.210
Holy crap, did you hear the big news?!

00:08:07.600 --> 00:08:11.420
The others girls in Spica are
bound to be worried about me.

00:08:11.900 --> 00:08:16.760
I can't keep sulking like this.
That won't change anything.

00:08:17.580 --> 00:08:21.190
But... even if I try harder...

00:08:23.860 --> 00:08:27.970
A distal tibial fracture in both legs with
an expected six months of recovery time.

00:08:27.970 --> 00:08:30.900
Word is that her chances of running
again this year are essentially gone.

00:08:32.280 --> 00:08:34.120
Again, for those just joining us,

00:08:32.280 --> 00:08:36.280
DURAMENTE INJURED
NO HOPE OF RUNNING AT THE KIKKASHOU?!

00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:36.500
we have learned the horse
girl who won the

00:08:36.280 --> 00:08:39.030
DURAMENTE INJURED

00:08:36.280 --> 00:08:39.030
NO HOPE OF RUNNING AT THE KIKKASHOU?!

00:08:36.500 --> 00:08:39.050
Double Crown at the Satsukishou
and Japanese Derby this year,

00:08:39.030 --> 00:08:40.540
DURAMENTE INJURED

00:08:39.030 --> 00:08:40.540
NO HOPE OF RUNNING AT THE KIKKASHOU?!

00:08:39.050 --> 00:08:41.200
Duramente, has broken her legs.

00:08:41.200 --> 00:08:42.970
Broken?

00:08:42.970 --> 00:08:46.430
The last race of the Classic
Triple Crown, the Kikkashou,

00:08:44.040 --> 00:08:52.550
DURAMENTE INJURED

00:08:44.040 --> 00:08:52.550
NO HOPE OF RUNNING AT THE KIKKASHOU?!

00:08:46.430 --> 00:08:49.100
is held in autumn and
said to be the main event,

00:08:49.100 --> 00:08:52.550
but now it seems there's
no telling what may happen.

00:08:52.760 --> 00:08:54.930
Duramente is a Double Crown horse
girl who has run in six races,

00:08:54.930 --> 00:08:57.770
with four wins and two second
place finishes, a dominant record,

00:08:57.770 --> 00:09:00.930
and was said to be the strongest
competitor in the Classic Triple Crown

00:09:00.930 --> 00:09:06.240
after her victories in the
Satsukishou and Japanese Derby.

00:09:06.240 --> 00:09:10.330
Naturally, this made her the favored
prospect for the Kikkashou in autumn,

00:09:10.330 --> 00:09:13.270
with fan expectations flying high,

00:09:13.270 --> 00:09:17.310
resulting in disappointment
after this recent development.

00:09:17.940 --> 00:09:21.960
It really is a shame, considering her
hopes for a Triple Crown.

00:09:23.010 --> 00:09:26.710
For our next story, tomorrow is
the long-anticipated grand prix,

00:09:26.710 --> 00:09:27.990
the Takarazuka Kinen...

00:09:27.530 --> 00:09:29.140
Pathetic.

00:09:27.990 --> 00:09:29.960
Voted the favorite race of
fans for two years in a row.

00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:33.960
Umamusume

00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:33.960
Pretty Derby

00:09:30.500 --> 00:09:33.180
I am just awful.

00:09:37.970 --> 00:09:41.000
She's so strong and fast though!
She's not gonna be in the Kikkashou?

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:44.380
No. Injuries are what they are,
but this is just awful.

00:09:45.670 --> 00:09:48.230
Kinda reminds me of what happened to Nature.

00:09:50.400 --> 00:09:53.030
I can't believe what happened to Duramente.

00:09:53.280 --> 00:09:55.780
I guess she won't be ready in time for fall.

00:09:55.780 --> 00:09:58.780
She would've had the Kikkashou
and Triple Crown in the bag.

00:09:58.780 --> 00:10:03.200
Still, this means the other horse girls
that are running have a chance now.

00:10:03.200 --> 00:10:04.660
Come on, man.

00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:09.530
I can't help but think about
what happened to Teio.

00:10:09.530 --> 00:10:11.250
I know what you mean! Me too!

00:10:11.250 --> 00:10:13.670
It's so awful. Poor Duramente.

00:10:13.670 --> 00:10:15.110
Really.

00:10:25.520 --> 00:10:27.430
Will Kita-san be okay?

00:10:27.430 --> 00:10:31.940
She's due back any time now, but when
she hears about Duramente's injury...

00:10:31.940 --> 00:10:33.520
She's bound to be frustrated.

00:10:33.520 --> 00:10:36.230
I'm sure she was thinking
about getting revenge.

00:10:36.230 --> 00:10:37.280
I think so.

00:10:37.500 --> 00:10:40.070
Wanting to run against someone,
but being unable to...

00:10:40.070 --> 00:10:43.410
I know all too well how painful that can be.

00:10:44.160 --> 00:10:46.420
Let's cheer her up when she gets back!

00:10:46.420 --> 00:10:47.940
"Don't sweat it, just run!"

00:10:47.940 --> 00:10:48.810
Good idea!

00:10:48.810 --> 00:10:52.920
Oh, I know! Why don't we make
a sports drink for Kita-san?

00:10:52.920 --> 00:10:54.040
I'm in!

00:10:59.030 --> 00:11:01.390
I'm... I'm so...

00:11:22.170 --> 00:11:24.520
Hey! You okay over there?

00:11:30.410 --> 00:11:33.240
Nice Nature-san...

00:11:34.670 --> 00:11:35.180
Oh, me!

00:11:35.180 --> 00:11:35.920
Turbo-san!

00:11:36.410 --> 00:11:37.420
Here.

00:11:38.330 --> 00:11:39.720
Thank you so much...

00:11:39.720 --> 00:11:41.220
Don't mention it.

00:11:41.220 --> 00:11:46.040
Tannhauser bought the tea, but we
honestly never drink the stuff.

00:11:50.170 --> 00:11:52.260
You don't wanna go to training?

00:11:53.270 --> 00:11:55.270
Guess you're a bit of a slacker!

00:11:58.220 --> 00:11:59.610
You thinking about the Kikkashou?

00:12:01.090 --> 00:12:03.970
This is a good chance to
get it off your chest.

00:12:03.970 --> 00:12:07.120
They say sometimes the less
familiar you are with someone,

00:12:07.120 --> 00:12:09.950
the easier it is to come clean with them.

00:12:09.950 --> 00:12:12.010
I'm all ears, if you're okay with that.

00:12:16.010 --> 00:12:17.130
It's bitter...

00:12:17.620 --> 00:12:19.220
She's my hero.

00:12:21.530 --> 00:12:24.730
I always wanted to be like Teio-san.

00:12:25.830 --> 00:12:28.150
I wanted to be a star like her.

00:12:29.370 --> 00:12:32.710
But I can't. I understand that now.

00:12:33.220 --> 00:12:37.170
Duramente-san is a lot more like her.

00:12:38.330 --> 00:12:40.770
Winning the Satsukishou and the Derby,

00:12:40.770 --> 00:12:44.810
with this incredible, cool running
style that makes everyone excited...

00:12:45.490 --> 00:12:47.530
The kind I could never do.

00:12:48.530 --> 00:12:51.070
And then when people heard about her legs,

00:12:51.070 --> 00:12:54.750
and learn that the Triple Crown isn't going
to happen, they're so disappointed...

00:12:54.750 --> 00:12:56.140
And worried.

00:12:57.090 --> 00:13:02.470
But I thought... "She really is like Teio-san."

00:13:03.040 --> 00:13:06.800
I realize how awful it must be to
be injured, and unable to run, and yet...

00:13:06.800 --> 00:13:09.880
But it's like everyone's only looking at her.

00:13:10.310 --> 00:13:14.310
And if that wasn't bad enough
of me, I actually thought...

00:13:14.730 --> 00:13:19.010
"If she isn't running, maybe now
I can win the Kikkashou."

00:13:19.010 --> 00:13:21.160
I actually thought that!

00:13:22.110 --> 00:13:25.450
I never had a chance in the first place!

00:13:25.940 --> 00:13:30.580
Not to become an impressive,
dazzling star like Teio-san!

00:13:36.630 --> 00:13:39.610
Wow. I completely get
where you're coming from.

00:13:41.340 --> 00:13:45.840
I looked up to Teio too, y'know.

00:13:48.590 --> 00:13:50.100
The thing about her...

00:13:50.500 --> 00:13:52.800
She's kind of a natural-born star?

00:13:53.130 --> 00:13:57.560
Shining and straightforward,
but she works hard too.

00:13:57.560 --> 00:13:59.280
And is really strong.

00:14:00.040 --> 00:14:03.220
But then she got injured during the Derby,

00:14:03.220 --> 00:14:07.070
and in spite of that, she worked hard
on her rehab until the very end.

00:14:07.650 --> 00:14:10.950
Watching her really made
me want to try harder.

00:14:11.580 --> 00:14:14.010
I thought, "I'm gonna run in the Kikkashou,
and I'm gonna win!"

00:14:14.830 --> 00:14:17.970
I actually managed to win four
races in a row after that,

00:14:17.970 --> 00:14:20.650
which got me into the Kikkashou!

00:14:22.800 --> 00:14:29.540
And then I started thinking...
"What if Teio isn't back in time?"

00:14:30.410 --> 00:14:33.100
That maybe I'd actually have
a chance in that case.

00:14:34.350 --> 00:14:37.110
I mean, I wanted to win. Who wouldn't?

00:14:37.480 --> 00:14:40.950
I wanted first place, not second or third.

00:14:41.460 --> 00:14:46.700
But... the second the idea came to mind,
I realized how lame that sounded.

00:14:46.700 --> 00:14:48.190
And I got mad...

00:14:49.320 --> 00:14:52.260
So yeah, I was in the same boat.

00:14:52.260 --> 00:14:53.460
Nature-san...

00:14:53.460 --> 00:15:00.120
It's rough, y'know? Getting compared to
these superstars like Teio and Duramente.

00:15:00.120 --> 00:15:02.220
People talk about how the star
of the Kikkashou is absent,

00:15:02.220 --> 00:15:05.960
or how they would've been guaranteed
to win if they could've ran.

00:15:06.830 --> 00:15:08.470
And I was like, "Screw that."

00:15:09.160 --> 00:15:12.720
So I was set on winning.
I wanted people to look at me.

00:15:13.050 --> 00:15:16.470
I wanted to show people that it
didn't matter if Teio was running.

00:15:16.800 --> 00:15:20.560
That was how I felt when I ran. I wanted
to show them what I was made of.

00:15:20.560 --> 00:15:24.730
As cowardly, or weak, or uncool as that
might've been... I was true to myself.

00:15:24.730 --> 00:15:27.870
I think that's where I really got started.

00:15:27.870 --> 00:15:29.780
Even though I only made fourth place.

00:15:30.650 --> 00:15:33.710
Your start... for being true to yourself.

00:15:34.900 --> 00:15:40.710
I don't know. I don't know
how to be true to myself...

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:45.020
It's a tough one. Even I still
wonder about it, from time to time.

00:15:45.020 --> 00:15:48.760
And I'm not confident at all.
Since the Derby, I've been so scared...

00:15:48.760 --> 00:15:52.730
I totally get that! I seriously don't know
if I've ever thought I could win for real.

00:15:52.730 --> 00:15:54.730
But... in spite of it all...

00:15:55.050 --> 00:15:58.310
I want to win.

00:15:58.890 --> 00:16:00.730
I still want to win!

00:16:00.730 --> 00:16:03.540
Yeah. Then you should show them.

00:16:03.540 --> 00:16:05.710
Everyone who thinks the
real star is missing...

00:16:05.710 --> 00:16:07.170
Do you think I can do it?

00:16:07.170 --> 00:16:11.270
You totally can! You've got a
much better shot than I did.

00:16:11.270 --> 00:16:14.260
Even if I'm cowardly, or weak, or uncool?

00:16:14.610 --> 00:16:19.130
All those things are a part
of Kitasan Black too, right?

00:16:19.130 --> 00:16:20.250
And that's you.

00:16:22.120 --> 00:16:25.660
I see... thank you so much.

00:16:25.660 --> 00:16:27.780
You're really nice, Nature-san!

00:16:27.780 --> 00:16:31.440
Aw, what're you talking about?!

00:16:31.440 --> 00:16:33.760
Go on, finish your tea!

00:16:33.760 --> 00:16:34.590
R-Right!

00:16:39.950 --> 00:16:40.730
Bitter!

00:16:40.730 --> 00:16:42.420
Right?

00:16:44.020 --> 00:16:46.100
She's still not back...

00:16:46.570 --> 00:16:49.520
I bet finding out about
Duramente really got to her.

00:16:49.520 --> 00:16:50.490
I think so.

00:16:50.490 --> 00:16:51.610
It's okay!

00:16:51.610 --> 00:16:54.950
I'm sure this sports
drink will perk her right up!

00:16:55.570 --> 00:16:56.870
I'm back!

00:16:56.870 --> 00:16:58.240
Kitasan...

00:16:59.780 --> 00:17:01.470
U-Um...

00:17:05.080 --> 00:17:07.280
I'm going to keep working hard!

00:17:07.280 --> 00:17:09.840
So I hope you'll keep instructing me!

00:17:10.880 --> 00:17:13.920
All right! You're gonna win that Kikkashou!

00:17:13.920 --> 00:17:15.180
Right!

00:17:15.180 --> 00:17:17.200
I'm gonna go run right now!

00:17:17.200 --> 00:17:18.970
Save it for tomorrow!

00:17:19.360 --> 00:17:22.570
I can't be like Teio-san.

00:17:22.910 --> 00:17:25.400
But I don't need to.

00:17:25.980 --> 00:17:29.080
I can be weak, and cowardly, and uncool...

00:17:29.080 --> 00:17:30.980
If that's who I am.

00:17:31.490 --> 00:17:36.740
Even if I'm not a star, and not
dazzling, and not the protagonist...

00:17:37.610 --> 00:17:39.980
I can fight... and struggle.

00:17:42.900 --> 00:17:46.040
And here we have the autumn G1 race.

00:17:46.040 --> 00:17:49.380
The last of the classic
triple crown, the Kikkashou!

00:17:49.380 --> 00:17:53.320
Duramente is unable to run due to injury,

00:17:53.320 --> 00:17:55.380
despite winning the Satsukishou
and Japanese Derby...

00:17:55.380 --> 00:17:59.640
And I'm sure there were many fans hoping
to see her win the Triple Crown.

00:17:59.640 --> 00:18:01.290
It really is a shame.

00:18:12.690 --> 00:18:15.190
No one needs to be paying attention.

00:18:15.770 --> 00:18:18.490
I don't care if anyone praises me.

00:18:19.700 --> 00:18:23.610
I'll fight as hard as I can... and I'll
do it my way. Being true to myself!

00:18:24.200 --> 00:18:27.200
The horse girls have entered their gates.

00:18:27.200 --> 00:18:29.360
As the cool fall breeze blows through Kyoto,

00:18:29.360 --> 00:18:34.110
who will win the Kikkashou, the final
race in the Classic Triple Crown?

00:18:34.910 --> 00:18:36.160
And they're off!

00:18:36.160 --> 00:18:39.040
Kindan Shirt makes a late start!

00:18:39.040 --> 00:18:42.250
She's going to be running far behind!

00:18:43.240 --> 00:18:45.720
Go!

00:18:44.070 --> 00:18:45.720
They're coming up on the corner,

00:18:45.720 --> 00:18:50.730
and it's Parole and Ribon Pastoral
battling for the lead!

00:18:50.730 --> 00:18:54.730
Are we looking at a war of attrition?
Parole and Ribon Pastoral pull out in front!

00:18:54.730 --> 00:18:56.230
They are both really going for it now!

00:18:56.230 --> 00:18:58.710
They say that the most powerful horse girl

00:18:58.710 --> 00:19:01.280
usually wins the final
race of the triple crown.

00:19:01.280 --> 00:19:02.290
Do you know why?

00:19:02.290 --> 00:19:03.120
What brought that on?

00:19:03.120 --> 00:19:05.550
It's because this race requires
both speed and stamina,

00:19:05.550 --> 00:19:08.330
with a length of 3,000 meters
that includes two hills,

00:19:08.330 --> 00:19:10.130
so you need to be the total package to win.

00:19:10.130 --> 00:19:13.280
It's also said that the race was
modeled after the St. Leger Stakes

00:19:13.280 --> 00:19:14.630
and that the Kyoto Ministry of—

00:19:14.630 --> 00:19:17.010
Go, Kitasan Black!

00:19:18.120 --> 00:19:22.010
How's she gonna do here? They seem
to be pulling away from her a bit.

00:19:22.010 --> 00:19:23.550
That's not necessarily a bad thing.

00:19:23.550 --> 00:19:25.410
Not necessarily good, either.

00:19:25.410 --> 00:19:26.580
Which is it?!

00:19:26.580 --> 00:19:29.770
The 3,000 meters for this
course aren't smooth going.

00:19:29.980 --> 00:19:34.150
Horse girls running the classics won't have
encountered a distance like this before.

00:19:34.150 --> 00:19:36.850
Then everyone has an equal opportunity...

00:19:36.850 --> 00:19:39.050
And now, with their thoughts and hopes

00:19:39.050 --> 00:19:41.020
pinned on the chrysanthemum
this race is named after,

00:19:41.020 --> 00:19:43.850
the horse girls are entering
the second corner!

00:19:43.850 --> 00:19:48.040
And as they ascend the second hill, the
placements are shifting all over the place!

00:19:48.250 --> 00:19:51.290
Fight! Struggle! Hang on!

00:19:51.290 --> 00:19:54.000
And run! Run! Run!

00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:56.870
The horse girls are now crossing
from the third to fourth corners,

00:19:56.870 --> 00:19:58.480
beginning their downhill descent.

00:19:58.480 --> 00:20:01.050
Genjitsu Steal seems to be conserving
her strength in the middle of the pack.

00:20:01.050 --> 00:20:03.680
I don't need to dazzle like a star!

00:20:04.040 --> 00:20:05.300
I'm just me!

00:20:05.300 --> 00:20:07.810
I'm Kitasan Black!

00:20:08.100 --> 00:20:11.560
Six hundred meters to go and they're
rounding the fourth curve!

00:20:11.560 --> 00:20:13.050
Go!

00:20:13.050 --> 00:20:16.380
And here's the final straightaway!
The horse girls enter their last spurt!

00:20:16.380 --> 00:20:19.570
On the inside, Kitasan Black is moving up!

00:20:23.030 --> 00:20:26.310
And this... is where it starts!

00:20:26.310 --> 00:20:28.200
Kitasan Black is making her move!

00:20:28.200 --> 00:20:32.510
Kitasan Black! Kitasan Black on the inside,
with Jewel Sapphire on the out,

00:20:32.510 --> 00:20:34.640
and Genjitsu Steal is coming up the middle!

00:20:34.640 --> 00:20:36.960
There's Genjitsu Steal in the center!

00:20:36.960 --> 00:20:39.560
Genjitsu Steal is tearing
up the center track!

00:20:39.960 --> 00:20:40.840
Kita-chan!

00:20:42.090 --> 00:20:43.340
Go!

00:20:46.840 --> 00:20:48.100
Go!

00:20:57.610 --> 00:20:59.320
Kitasan Black has the lead!

00:20:59.320 --> 00:21:01.190
She's holding it!

00:21:01.190 --> 00:21:04.080
It's a festival! This is
looking like a festival!

00:21:04.080 --> 00:21:06.950
It's Kitasan's festival!

00:21:04.760 --> 00:21:06.950
Kikkashou

00:21:06.950 --> 00:21:10.080
Kitasan Black is your winner!

00:21:10.080 --> 00:21:11.330
Kita-chan!

00:21:35.570 --> 00:21:36.730
Well...

00:21:37.130 --> 00:21:39.230
You seem pretty dazzling to me.

00:21:42.360 --> 00:21:45.640
See what I meant? Kita-chan was just fine.

00:21:45.640 --> 00:21:48.490
I suppose we were worried for nothing.

00:21:50.090 --> 00:21:55.140
Y'know, maybe Kita-chan will end up
an even better horse girl than me.

00:21:55.140 --> 00:21:57.750
You won't tell her that?

00:21:58.080 --> 00:21:59.680
Why would I?! I'm jealous!

00:22:11.350 --> 00:22:13.640
Thank you so much!

00:22:14.350 --> 00:22:16.300
This is where I get my start.

00:22:16.790 --> 00:22:20.860
Even if I'm not cool,
I'll still be moving forward.

00:22:20.860 --> 00:22:21.980
For me, this is...

00:22:21.980 --> 00:22:24.980
Episode 2

00:22:21.980 --> 00:22:24.980
The Start Line

